One rainy afternoon, a new girl named Lily moved into the house next door. She carried a sketchbook and a stack of watercolor paints. When Ethan saw her, he was curious. “What are you drawing?” he asked.

Lily smiled and opened her sketchbook. “I’m trying to capture the clouds that look like cotton candy,” she said. “They’re so soft, but they’re also moving, changing shape.”

Ethan laughed. “You’re talking about clouds, and I’m talking about my pillow. Both are soft, but only one can lift you.”

Lily nodded. “Maybe that’s the point. A pillow keeps you grounded, while a cloud lifts you. Both need each other to make a good day.”

