Ethan felt a warmth he’d never felt before. He understood that love was not just a pillow that you lay on or a cloud that you imagine. It was the act of giving, the willingness to share, and the gentle support that lifts people up when they’re feeling down.

When he went back to his room that night, he pressed the pillow to his chest and whispered, “Thank you, Cloud.” He smiled, realizing that the pillow was indeed a cloud, but the real cloud was the love he’d found in Lily and the old lady. It was a cloud that lifted him, not just in imagination, but in reality.

